---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'network-and-claims', text: 'Network and Claims', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-should-choose', text: 'Who Should Choose Which', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Verdict', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Best Digital Nomad Insurance', href: '/best/digital-nomad-insurance' },
  { title: 'Portugal Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/portugal/insurance' },
  { title: 'Spain Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/spain/insurance' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing Nomad' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { feature: 'Type', safetywing: 'Travel Medical', cigna: 'Health Insurance' },
  { feature: 'Maximum Coverage', safetywing: '$250,000', cigna: 'Unlimited (Platinum)' },
  { feature: 'Commitment', safetywing: 'None (cancel anytime)', cigna: 'Annual' },
  { feature: 'Outpatient Care', safetywing: 'Emergency only', cigna: 'Gold/Platinum' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', safetywing: 'Not covered', cigna: 'Included' },
  { feature: 'Maternity', safetywing: 'Not covered', cigna: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Pre-existing', safetywing: 'Not covered', cigna: 'Underwritten' },
  { feature: 'Direct Billing', safetywing: 'Limited', cigna: '1.5M+ providers' },
  { feature: 'Customer Service', safetywing: 'Email/chat', cigna: '24/7 phone' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing Nomad' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Gold (ex-US)' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Age 30', safetywing: '$45/4 weeks', cigna: '$140-200/mo' },
  { profile: 'Age 40', safetywing: '$76/4 weeks', cigna: '$220-300/mo' },
  { profile: 'Age 50', safetywing: '$117/4 weeks', cigna: '$350-450/mo' },
  { profile: 'Age 60', safetywing: '$189/4 weeks', cigna: '$500-650/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing vs Cigna Global"
  description="Compare SafetyWing and Cigna Global side by side. Startup travel insurance vs traditional health coverage—which approach fits your needs?"
  headline="SafetyWing vs Cigna Global: Nomad vs Traditional"
  subheadline="The scrappy digital nomad favorite versus the established global giant. Completely different products at completely different price points."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes from Both"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
    <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing and Cigna Global are both popular choices for international health insurance, but they serve different needs. Understanding their key differences will help you choose the right coverage for your situation abroad.
  </p>
  <p>
    SafetyWing is a modern insurance option designed specifically for digital nomads and remote workers. Their main subscription-based model with no long-term commitment required. They're particularly popular among digital nomads, remote workers, and location-independent professionals, with very affordable monthly subscription starting around $40/month.
  </p>
  <p>
    Cigna Global is known for its extensive global network and strong customer service. They're known for their massive provider network with direct billing at over 1.5 million healthcare facilities worldwide. They tend to attract families and American expats who prioritize convenience, offering premium pricing but many feel the convenience justifies the cost.
  </p>
  <p>
    This comparison breaks down the key differences between these two providers so you can make an informed decision. We'll cover coverage options, pricing estimates, network access, claims processes, and help you determine which one makes more sense for your specific needs and budget.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">SafetyWing Nomad Insurance</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li><strong>Type:</strong> Travel medical insurance</li>
        <li>Founded 2017 (startup)</li>
        <li>Subscription-based, cancel anytime</li>
        <li>$250,000 maximum coverage</li>
        <li>Simple, transparent pricing</li>
        <li>Built for digital nomads</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Cigna Global</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li><strong>Type:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance</li>
        <li>Decades of global experience</li>
        <li>Annual commitment</li>
        <li>Unlimited coverage available</li>
        <li>1.5M+ provider network</li>
        <li>Premium customer service</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Different Products, Different Purposes</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      <strong>SafetyWing Nomad Insurance is travel medical insurance</strong>—it covers emergencies while traveling. <strong>Cigna Global is full health insurance</strong>—it covers your complete healthcare needs. SafetyWing costs less because it covers less. This isn't a case of "same thing, different price."
    </p>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Both Options"
    description="Get quotes to see the actual price difference for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="coverage-comparison">Coverage Comparison</h2>
  <p>
    The coverage gap between SafetyWing and Cigna is substantial. Cigna offers comprehensive health insurance; SafetyWing offers emergency travel coverage.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>What this means in practice:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Doctor visits:</strong> Cigna covers routine visits; SafetyWing only covers emergencies</li>
    <li><strong>Prescriptions:</strong> Cigna covers ongoing medications; SafetyWing covers acute-illness prescriptions only</li>
    <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> Cigna includes it; SafetyWing doesn't cover it at all</li>
    <li><strong>Serious illness:</strong> Cigna's unlimited coverage handles anything; SafetyWing's $250K could run out with cancer or major surgery</li>
    <li><strong>Pre-existing conditions:</strong> Cigna underwrites them (may cover with exclusions); SafetyWing excludes them entirely</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>SafetyWing Remote Health Alternative</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing also offers <strong>Remote Health</strong>, which is actual health insurance (not travel medical). Remote Health has coverage up to $10M, includes mental health and maternity, and covers pre-existing conditions after a waiting period. Remote Health competes more directly with Cigna, at $100-700/month. If you like SafetyWing's approach but need real health insurance, Remote Health is worth considering.
  </p>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing is dramatically cheaper—but you're paying for different things.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>The price-to-coverage ratio:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>SafetyWing at age 30: ~$49/month for $250K emergency coverage</li>
    <li>Cigna Gold at age 30: ~$170/month for comprehensive health coverage</li>
    <li>That's 3.5x more for Cigna—but Cigna covers exponentially more</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    <strong>Ways to reduce Cigna's cost:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Higher deductibles ($5,000-$10,000) can reduce premiums 25-35%</li>
    <li>Excluding US coverage saves 40-60%</li>
    <li>Silver tier (inpatient only) is cheaper than Gold</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">When Cigna's Cost Makes Sense</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      If you're over 40, have any health conditions, or want peace of mind for serious illness, Cigna's higher cost is justified. One hospitalization for a serious condition could easily exceed SafetyWing's $250K limit—at which point you'd be paying out of pocket. Cigna's unlimited coverage means you're protected no matter what happens.
    </p>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your Actual Price"
    description="See the real cost difference for your age and needs."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="network-and-claims">Network and Claims</h2>

  <h3>Provider Networks</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna Global</strong> has 1.5 million+ providers worldwide with extensive direct-billing relationships. Walk into a network hospital, show your card, and Cigna handles the payment. Their network is particularly strong in Europe, Asia, and the Middle East.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing</strong> coordinates with hospitals for major emergencies, but most claims are reimbursement-based. You pay, then submit a claim. For smaller treatments, expect to pay out of pocket and wait for reimbursement.
  </p>

  <h3>Claims Experience</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna:</strong> User-friendly online portal and app. Claims typically processed in 5-10 days. Direct billing eliminates most claims for major procedures. Known for responsive, professional service.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Simple online claims portal. Processing can take 10-30 days. Mixed reviews—straightforward for small claims, but some users report delays or denials requiring appeals. More typical of budget insurance.
  </p>

  <h3>Customer Service</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna:</strong> 24/7 phone support in multiple languages. Dedicated customer service teams. White-glove service for complex situations. This is premium support.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Email and chat support during business hours. No 24/7 phone line. Adequate for basic questions, but not the premium experience. They're a startup—act accordingly.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-should-choose">Who Should Choose Which</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose SafetyWing If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You're young (under 35) and very healthy</li>
        <li>You just need emergency coverage, not healthcare</li>
        <li>You're testing the nomad lifestyle short-term</li>
        <li>Budget is your primary concern</li>
        <li>You want zero commitment—cancel anytime</li>
        <li>You have access to affordable local healthcare</li>
        <li>You're comfortable with reimbursement claims</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose Cigna Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You need actual health insurance</li>
        <li>You're over 40 or have any health concerns</li>
        <li>You want mental health coverage</li>
        <li>Family coverage matters</li>
        <li>You want direct billing at hospitals</li>
        <li>You need high or unlimited coverage limits</li>
        <li>Premium customer service is worth paying for</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing and Cigna Global aren't competitors—they're different products serving different needs at different price points.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing Nomad Insurance</strong> is excellent for its purpose: affordable emergency coverage for healthy travelers. If you're 28, have no health issues, and just want a safety net while bouncing between Bali and Lisbon, SafetyWing delivers good value. It's the Honda Civic of travel insurance—reliable, affordable, gets the job done.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna Global</strong> is comprehensive health insurance for people who want full coverage. If you're settling abroad long-term, have a family, are over 40, or want peace of mind that you're covered for anything, Cigna provides that security. It's the premium choice—you pay more and get more.
  </p>
  <p>
    The question isn't which is "better"—it's which matches your needs. A 25-year-old healthy nomad spending a year traveling doesn't need Cigna. A 50-year-old with a family moving to Portugal for five years shouldn't rely on SafetyWing. Choose the product that fits your life stage and risk tolerance.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-100 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Middle Ground: SafetyWing Remote Health</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-700">
      If you want something between these extremes, SafetyWing's <strong>Remote Health</strong> product offers comprehensive health insurance (not travel medical) with coverage up to $10M, mental health included, and a subscription-friendly approach. At $100-700/month, it's cheaper than Cigna while providing real health coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Decide?"
    description="Compare quotes based on your specific situation and needs."
    buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices, coverage, and plan details change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify all information with the providers before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
